JOHANNESBURG – Burning tyres are blocking roads in Alexandra as a protest is underway at the Central Johannesburg College's Alexandra Campus. Students are angry about what they claim is the maladministration of funds. READ: Take free education 'by force': Fees Must Fall activist They are also concerned about accommodation problems, with allegations that landlords have not been paid. The protesters are demanding senior management step down. The Johannesburg Metro Police has advised motorists to avoid London Road and 13th Avenue. JHB - #ProtestAction Alexandra: (Update): RT @wendyyah London Rd in Alex is closed @TrafficSA -- ROAD CLOSED eNCA